 On 15Apr2016 8:53 pm, "Rakesh Vakr" <rocky13795@gmail.com wrote:

 A few things.

 i) Permission was granted to us till 10PM and not 8PM as wrongly
 stated in the initial mail. And as our exsocsecs will assure you, our
 warden is very supportive of us participating in cultural activities. 
Also,
 over the past couple of years, hostel music practice happened over two
 months, and not a few days like this time (sadly). We never had any
 complaints, since the inhabitants of Ganga understood that this is a
 hostel, and certain compromises had to be made to support mates who ar
e
 representing the spirit of Ganga. (GO GANGA!)

 ii) We too, just like everyone else have classes in the morning and
 labs till the evening (quite surprising? I think not), so practising a
t
 these times is definitely out of the question.

 iii) We too have exams, assignments, reports, submissions,
 deadlines, internship interviews and what not along with Saarang/Shaas
tra
 app deadlines. Heck, I'm losing count of the number of sleepless night
s
 I've had for the same reasons. We are taking time out of our schedules
 for
 the hostel to participate in these events, and the least we could have
 is
 some compromise from our hostel mates, instead of relentless cribs. Wh
en
 you came down and unceremoniously disrupted our sessions and asked us 
to
 reduce the volume, we did. We have been lowering volumes repeatedly
 since you guys complained.

 iv) @ArjunAR, we've had several people come down to the music room
 from their rooms or the quadi to listen to us. All of them said we sou
nd
 nice. So I'm going to make the statistically safe option of assuming y
ou
 are quite tonedeaf.

 v) These incidents are strongly reminding me of my childhood and
 those neighbourhood aunties and uncles who used to scream at my friend
s and
 I for playing football and cricket on the streets. Not so desirable
 nostalgia, to be blatantly honest.

 PS 1  If you have any cribs, please contact me at +919962615051 and
 let me know, instead of bursting in like you own the hostel.

 PS 2  Again, GO GANGA!

 Godspeed
 Vakr


